        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 13 at 5:01PM EDT by NWS Caribou ME</headline>
        <description>At 501 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Van Buren, moving northeast at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Van Buren, Grand Isle, Connor, Stockholm, Hamlin, and Cyr Plantation.

This includes US Highway 1 near Van Buren.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
